      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of NIH output to key input parameters (viscosity, power-law coefficients) documented.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2. Nominal input values sourced from peer-reviewed literature. Formal sensitivity analysis and input uncertainty propagation deferred per MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Number of experimental replicates and statistical treatment of measurement variability documented.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed at MRL 2. FDA GCBP experimental dataset provides single-run measurements at each operating point. Replicate statistics not required at this model risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mapping between experimental and simulation input parameters documented with any discrepancies and their impact on QoI addressed.",
      "rationale": "Experimental fluid (bovine blood analog, Hct 30%) mapped to simulation Newtonian viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s) using Quemada model at relevant shear rates. Discrepancy in non-Newtonian behavior at low shear assessed as negligible for high-shear impeller region driving hemolysis."
    }
  ],
